COMMAND LINE INTERPRETER : cmd.exe

CHECK PATH : set

CHECK VERSION : ver

CHECK DETAILED INFO : systeminfo

VIEW PAGE BY PAGE : Command | more

CLEAR : cls

COMMAND HELP : commandName /?


SHOW IP MAC SUBNET GATEWAY : ipconfig 

SHOW DHCP AND DNS TOO : ipconfig \all

CHECK CONNECTION : ping IP_WebLink

TRACE NETWORK ROUTE : tracert IP_WebLink

RETURN IP BY DEFAULT SERVER : nslookup WebLink

RETURN IP BY SOECIFIC SERVER : nslookup WebLink ServerIP

NETSTAT : 

    nestat -a : displays all established connections and listening ports
    nestat -b : shows the program associated with each listening port and established connection
    nestat -o : reveals the process ID (PID) associated with the connection
    nestat -n : uses a numerical form for addresses and port numbers

GET SPECIFIC PORT CONNECTION : netstat -aon | findstr :PORT

GET SERVICE WITH PID : tasklist /svc /FI "PID eq PID_FROM_ABOVE_COMMAND"


CHANGE DIRECTORY : cd \Path\

LIST CONTENTS : dir \Path\

CREATE FOLDER : mkdir FolderName

DELETE FOLDER : rmdir FolderName

READ FILE : type Filename

COPY FILES OR FOLDER : copy \Path_Source\ \Path_Destination\

MOVE FILES OR FOLDER : move \Path_Source\ \Path_Destination\

DELETE FILES : del OR erase Filename


LIST RUNNING PROCESSES: tasklist

APPLY FILTER : tasklist /FI "imagename eq  ProcessName"

TERMINATE PROCESS : taskkill /PID PID_PROCESS


chkdsk: checks the file system and disk volumes for errors and bad sectors.
driverquery: displays a list of installed device drivers.
sfc /scannow: scans system files for corruption and repairs them if possible.

SHUTDOWN SYSTEM : shutdown /s

ABORT SCHEDULED SHUTDOWN : shutdown /a

RESTART : shutdown /r